Hi! Iâ€™m a Postdoctoral Research Fellow at SAIL/MCIS Lab in the School of Computing at Queen's University, Kingston, Canada.

My current research focuses on agentic software engineering, specifically the Agent Control Environment (ACE), where humans interact with agents, and the Agent Execution Environment (AEE), where different agents and tools collaborate to perform complex software engineering tasks.Â 

My earlier research focused on applying AI techniques to automated software engineering (AI4SE). In particular, I investigate the reliability and trustworthiness of foundation models and large language models in tasks such as text-to-source-code generation, unit test and test-oracle (assertion) generation, explainable defect prediction, automatic program repair, code summarization, and code translation.
